 &quot;cries because he traded TBB for Wurmslayer yak and mithril arms&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zipherius>Zipherius</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/24/00 5:42:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons 1hsvs2hs</span><hr size=1> Tbb is tradeable for wurmslayer? *Goes and farms TBB*  Anyway 1hs is proably better in the long run.  But I would get a cheap 2hs (blade of xalgox is good for this) and a cheap 2hb like a mithril staff.  Its best to keep all your skills up but generally I find myself doing more dammage with 1hs.  And I think you got a great deal on that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unorok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norok</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ironcross.org/images/ironcross.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/24/00 6:13:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons 1hsvs2hs</span><hr size=1> My Damage per second on the Granite Face Grinder and the Oggok Cleaver is higher then Dual Lamentations.<br>
<br>
My thoughts <br>
<br>
You can do more damage with a 2 Handed Weapon however you taunt alot better and duel better with fast 1 Handed weapons.<br>
<br>
I recommend keeping all your skills maxed - you never know when a Granite Face Grinder 29/36 +10 str/wis/int or another weapon like it will fall into your lap. And before Kunark I am willing to bet you could count the number of Warriors that worked 2hb on each server with one hand.<br>
<br>
One of the weapons I traded away (for Runebanded Girdle, Darkscale Greaves and Arbitors Combine Sword) was a Rod of Mourning. 29/36 +5 str +5 wis +6int -5 agi +25 hp +25 mana effect Force (83 point Stun) - 2 Hand Blunt...<br>
<br>
So best to keep all the skills up and use whatever weapon you have at the time that meets the purpose whether that purpose is to deal out mass damage or to taunt'n tank. <p><b>Da Rok</b><br>
<br>
Nurok SkulKrusher 51st Level Ogre Champion<br>
Norok LightBringer 53rd Level Dwarven Vicar<br>
<b>Knights of the Iron Cross</b><br>
<b>The Rathe</b>
<p><img border="0" src="http://www.mhtc.net/~khorne/nurok.jpg" width="246" height="104"></image>
</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zipherius>Zipherius</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/24/00 6:23:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons 1hsvs2hs</span><hr size=1> Yeah keep weapons maxed.  Its a pain to have to raise 1hb and 2hb from 0.  Took me like 20 levels to raise 1hs to 200.  Anyway Keep all weapons maxed to maximise potental.<br>
<br>
Zipherius Thaladar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukorrellian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korrellian</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/25/00 10:26:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/korrellian2000/pic5.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons 1hsvs2hs</span><hr size=1> You are on the right track; to couple with a Wurmslayer stick to either a good proc'ng weapon or a stat builder.  I use a GJB.<br>
 <p>Korrellian Kullraven<BR>Warchief, Sabretooth Bear Clan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukorrellian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korrellian</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/25/00 10:33:47 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/korrellian2000/pic5.jpg height=36 width=38></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons 1hsvs2hs</span><hr size=1> Then again a good 2 hander would be better against those buggers with damage sheilds.<br>
<br>
 <p>Korrellian Kullraven<BR>Warchief, Sabretooth Bear Clan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=talicmoore>Talic Moore</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/25/00 4:27:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Preference.</span><hr size=1> I'm surprised I did'nt see this topic earlier. Normally I'll use a very fast 2hs (Nathar Greatsword + FBSS is my favorite) but seems like lately I use my Wurmslayer/Kunzar Ku'Juch combo. If you have the WS I would recommend using it for the time being, maybe get a snaring weapon (Silken Whip or Kunzar) or something with a nice proc (Ykesha etc)<br>
<br>
Talic Moore<br>
Half-Elven warrior of the 47th Cael<br>
Lord Decurion of the Kalrathi Blademasters<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uathasicebeast.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Athas Icebeast</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/00 10:38:06 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.users.uswest.net/~jlorfing/members/athas.jpg WIDTH=48 HEIGHT=211></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Preference.</span><hr size=1> wurmslayer is a cool weapon to show off with, but I didn't not like the low taunt on it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
when using weapons that have low delay plus a haste item, you can taunt like crazy...with ws you just do demonic damage, but your taunt works less <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   i remember back in the release when i hit level 10, i knew i was never gonna be a damage dealer, i was gonna be a damage taker...so i will sacrafice damage for tanking/taunting abillity.  if I wanna do crazy dmg, i go play my mage. hehe, simple as that<br>
<br>
as someone also said, fast weapons win duels...<br>
 <p><font size=5><font color=white><left><u><b>Athas Icebeast</u></b></left></font></font><br>

<left><b>T'Kagi Ro Officer</left><br>

<left><b>The Pride of Halas</b></left><br>

<left><i>"I should be able to use gnomes as 1hb weapons!!!"</i></left></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubaarakorchammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaarakOrchammer</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/12/00 1:07:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Preference.</span><hr size=1> You know I hear a lot of people state that they do not like WS due to the taunt factor. I have not had this problem. Using a WS and cane of the tranquil I am rarely not able to taunt a mob off my casters. <br>
<br>
I am pretty careful about timing my taunts these days and it really does help keeping the mob interested.<br>
<br>
Baarak Orchammer<br>
Wolf of the North <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utrueheart78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>trueheart78</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/drahk78/dance.gif WIDTH=15 HEIGHT=24 BORDER=0></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/13/00 7:32:20 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/drahk78/hobbes1.gif WIDTH=67 HEIGHT=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Preference.</span><hr size=1> Yes, Wurmslayer is underrated nowadays. Seems like EVERYONE has them. Alot of people wanna try &amp; be different, and go for the weapons that will be abit more standoutish.<br>
<br>
Hey, I fall into that category. Wurm is fine IMO, but I don't care to use it. yes I know I am not doing the dmg, providing that lil extra amount of ac or such, but, I have alot of FUN playing around with my weaponry, and well, I honestly think wurm would be bagged more than my mith staff. <p><DIV ALIGN="center"><A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/drahk78/locate.html" TARGET="top"><IMG SRC="http://www.geocities.com/drahk78/duosig2.jpg" BORDER=0></A></DIV ALIGN="left"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uclubberlang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Clubber Lang</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/SouthBeach/Cove/6155/pics/tlep12.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/00 8:05:41 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/SouthBeach/Cove/6155/pics/tlep12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Preference.</span><hr size=1>   Weapons such as this <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/fangol.html">www.gameznet.com/eq/equip...angol.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
(29/35 STR:3 Dex:10 PR:10 STA:10 + 120 point DD to those too lazy to look for yourselves :P)<br>
<br>
make 2 handers superior, not to mention the upgrade in dmg bonus for them.  <br>
<br>
